From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Fennec Authors <patches@fennec.computer>
Date: Mon, 08 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] privacy: enable WebRTC IP leak protection by default

WebRTC can expose a user's real local IP address even when behind a VPN
by enumerating network interfaces during ICE candidate gathering. This
patch sets the default WebRTC IP handling policy to
DISABLE_NON_PROXIED_UDP, which forces all WebRTC traffic through any
configured proxy and suppresses local IP candidates.

This may affect peer-to-peer connections (video calls, gaming) that
rely on direct LAN routing. Users can relax it via:
  Settings → Privacy → WebRTC IP handling policy

Chromium default: DEFAULT (exposes all IPs)
Fennec default:   DISABLE_NON_PROXIED_UDP

PILLAR: Privacy
JOURNAL: none

---
 chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc b/chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc
index 2c3d4e5f..7a8b9c0d 100644
--- a/chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc
+++ b/chrome/browser/profiles/profile_impl.cc
@@ -425,6 +425,14 @@ void ProfileImpl::RegisterProfilePrefs(
+  // Fennec: set WebRTC IP handling to DISABLE_NON_PROXIED_UDP by default.
+  // Chromium stores this as an integer matching
+  // blink::mojom::WebRTCIPHandlingPolicy enum.
+  //   0 = DEFAULT (exposes all IPs)
+  //   1 = DEFAULT_PUBLIC_AND_PRIVATE_INTERFACES
+  //   2 = DEFAULT_PUBLIC_INTERFACE_ONLY
+  //   3 = DISABLE_NON_PROXIED_UDP  ← Fennec default
+  registry->RegisterIntegerPref(
+      prefs::kWebRTCIPHandlingPolicy,
+      3,  // DISABLE_NON_PROXIED_UDP
+      user_prefs::PrefRegistrySyncable::SYNCABLE_PREF);
 }
